name: Verfiy GET external Chat API returns 404
description:
### Pre-conditions:
- DeepSeek app installed.

### Steps:
- Login with valid credentials.
- GET `external` OpenAI Compatible Chat API `hostname` link.

### Verify that:

- API response status is 404.
descriptionHtml:
Pre-conditions:

  • DeepSeek app installed.

Steps:

  • Login with valid credentials.
  • GET external OpenAI Compatible Chat API hostname link.

Verify that:

  • API response status is 404.
statusMessage:
AssertionError: [ClientConnectorDNSError] during step: Verify GET external Compatible Chat API returns 404
Message: Cannot connect to host none:443 ssl:default [DNS server returned general failure]
statusTrace:
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/resolver.py:117: in resolve
    resp = await self._resolver.getaddrinfo(
E   aiodns.error.DNSError: (3, 'DNS server returned general failure')

The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/connector.py:1562: in _create_direct_connection
    hosts = await self._resolve_host(host, port, traces=traces)
            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/connector.py:1178: in _resolve_host
    return await asyncio.shield(resolved_host_task)
           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/connector.py:1209: in _resolve_host_with_throttle
    addrs = await self._resolver.resolve(host, port, family=self._family)
            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/resolver.py:126: in resolve
    raise OSError(None, msg) from exc
E   OSError: [Errno None] DNS server returned general failure

The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:
tests/reporting_hooks/reporting.py:49: in wrapper
    result = await func(*args, **kwargs)
             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
tests/test_cases/steps/api_steps/api_steps.py:420: in verify_external_chat_api_not_found
    status, response = await self._api_helper._get(token=token, endpoint=endpoint)
                       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
tests/utils/api_helper.py:56: in _get
    async with self._session.get(
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/client.py:1510: in __aenter__
    self._resp: _RetType = await self._coro
                           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/client.py:779: in _request
    resp = await handler(req)
           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/client.py:734: in _connect_and_send_request
    conn = await self._connector.connect(
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/connector.py:672: in connect
    proto = await self._create_connection(req, traces, timeout)
            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/connector.py:1239: in _create_connection
    _, proto = await self._create_direct_connection(req, traces, timeout)
               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/aiohttp/connector.py:1568: in _create_direct_connection
    raise ClientConnectorDNSError(req.connection_key, exc) from exc
E   aiohttp.client_exceptions.ClientConnectorDNSError: Cannot connect to host none:443 ssl:default [DNS server returned general failure]

The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:
tests/test_cases/tests_e2e/test_deep_seek_app.py:479: in test_ext_chat_endpoint_not_found
    await api_steps.verify_external_chat_api_not_found(
tests/reporting_hooks/reporting.py:58: in wrapper
    raise AssertionError(formatted_msg) from e
E   AssertionError: [ClientConnectorDNSError] during step: Verify GET external Compatible Chat API returns 404
E   Message: Cannot connect to host none:443 ssl:default [DNS server returned general failure]
